int32_t gaia::core::RunningAppProcessInfo::getImportance ( )

The relative importance level that the system places on this process.

May be one of enumImportance. These constants are numbered so that "more important" values are always smaller than "less important" values.

int32_t gaia::core::RunningAppProcessInfo::getImportanceReasonCode ( )

bool gaia::core::RunningAppProcessInfo::getImportanceReasonComponent ( ComponentName  cname)

For the specified values of importanceReasonCode, this is the name of the component that is being used in this process.

int32_t gaia::core::RunningAppProcessInfo::getImportanceReasonPid ( )

For the specified values of importanceReasonCode, this is the process ID of the other process that is a client of this process.

This will be 0 if no other process is using this one.

int32_t gaia::core::RunningAppProcessInfo::getLru ( )

An additional ordering within a particular importance category, providing finer-grained information about the relative utility of processes within a category.

This number means nothing except that a smaller values are more recently used (and thus more important). Currently an LRU value is only maintained for the RunningAppProcessInfo::IMPORTANCE_BACKGROUND category, though others may be maintained in the future.
